      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 25:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "nor discover his father's skirt; or lie with her his father had thrown his skirt over, or married; and which being the first, is mentioned here as a sample to all the rest forbidden Leviticus 18:7 or, as Bishop Patrick expresses it, is a \"short memorandum\", to make them careful to observe all the other laws respecting incestuous marriages and copulations there delivered. ",
